<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> in half • in halves</xh5><p> <i>in half—</i>1. <i>divide or tear </i>into two equal parts: He and Meyer each signed half of a one dollar bill, tore it <u>in half</u> and kept each other’s halves, just for good luck. 2. <i>(also: by half )</i> reduce by fifty percent of the original amount: He had priced rolltops in a downtown department store and knew he had cut the cost <u>in half</u>.</p><p> <i>in halves</i>— = in half 1: When a square cut <u>in halves</u> makes two triangles, those two triangles are still only the two halves of the square.</p> </entry>
